<title>NETHERLANDS: CYCLING-RIIS WINS AMSTEL AFTER SOLO BREAK.</title>
<headline>CYCLING-RIIS WINS AMSTEL AFTER SOLO BREAK.</headline>
<dateline>MAASTRICHT, Netherlands 1997-04-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bjarne Riis of Denmark won the 258-km Amstel Gold World Cup race on Saturday, cruising across the finish line with his arms aloft after a 35-km solo break.</p>
<p>Riis, the 1996 Tour de France winner, finished ahead of Italy's Andrea Tafi in second and Beat Zberg of Switzerland in third.</p>
<p>The Dane raced away from an eight-man lead group about 35 kms from the finish and rode through buffeting winds and rain-soaked roads unchallenged by the chasers.</p>
